div.p: The Magic Constraint: Step 2 happens AFTER the state is set to TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE in Step 1. If a writer signals between 0 and 1, Step 2 detects it and aborts the sleep.
CPU Context: Process A (Reader) task_struct->state: TASK_RUNNING dev_mutex: FREE (Unlocked)
task_struct->state: TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE read_queue: [ wait_entry_A ] (Linked) Stack: wait_queue_entry_t allocated on Reader stack
Logic: if (buffer_used > f_pos) Observation: Racy read of buffer_used WITHOUT mutex. Invariant: If writer ran between Step 0 and 1, condition is now TRUE. Path: If TRUE -> Jump to Step 6 (No Sleep).
Logic: if (signal_pending(current)) Action: Check TIF_SIGPENDING flag in thread info. Path: If pending -> Jump to Step 7.
Scheduler: deactivate_task(Process A) Process A: REMOVED from RunQueue CPU: Context switches to another task. Wait: Process A sleeps until wake_up_interruptible().
Trigger: Writer called wake_up_interruptible(read_queue) Scheduler: activate_task(Process A) task_struct->state: TASK_RUNNING Loop: Returns to Step 2 to verify condition under lock.
